Tier 6 — Procedural Sovereignty
Module 62 – Filing Cadence: A Weekly Rhythm that Builds Pressure 🎼📄
⚖️ Core Message
A steady cadence outperforms bursts. One precise brick per week—filed—beats a month of drafting that never lands on the docket.

📖 Lesson Content
• Scope Small — Micro‑asks (accept corrected index; set status call; permit sur‑reply).
• Cadence Board — Kanban lanes: Draft → Proof → File → Follow‑up → Archive.
• Friday Rule — If in doubt, place one brick by end of week; build momentum.
• Revisit — Convert clerk emails to Notices; convert refusals to Requests for Order.
• Archive Echo — Publish summary + hash after each brick to grow coalition.
📝 Assignment
Implement a 4‑week cadence board and commit to one filed page per week (Decision Cover + Order A/B).

✅ Model Answer (Template)
CADENCE CARD
Week 1: Paper Hearing Q&A
Week 2: Motion to Accept Corrected Filing
Week 3: Jurisdiction Statement
Week 4: Status Call Request.

💡 Reflection
Cadence is compounding interest for procedure.

🎨 Visual Pairing
Kanban board with weekly 'File' column highlighted.



