Module 63
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 6 — Procedural Sovereignty
Module 63 – Multi‑Jurisdiction Service: Crossing Lines Without Losing Proof 🌍📬
⚖️ Core Message
Serving across states or systems means consistent proof: method, tracking, and declarations that travel to any forum.

📖 Lesson Content
• Rule Matrix — FRCP 4/5 + state analogs; certified mail vs personal service.
• Stipulated Email — Get it in writing; attach the stipulation to your COS.
• International Hints — Hague basics (if relevant); keep this module high‑level.
• Proof Pack — Affidavit, receipts, headers; one PDF with bookmarks.
• Fallback — If in doubt, double‑serve (mail + email) with clear labeling.
📝 Assignment
Draft a cross‑border COS with exhibits for two recipients (counsel + agency), using mail + stipulated email.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
COS (EXCERPT)
Service by USPS Certified #____ and stipulated email to counsel@firm.com; Affidavit attached.

💡 Reflection
No forum can ignore clean, verifiable service proof.

🎨 Visual Pairing
An envelope icon spanning two map regions with a barcode overlay.



