Module 66
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 6 — Procedural Sovereignty
Module 66 – Docket Watchers: Detect, Log, and Act on Changes 👀📜
⚖️ Core Message
Don’t discover docket changes by accident. Set watchers, log deltas, and file a short note when critical entries appear—or disappear.

📖 Lesson Content
• Watch Methods — Manual sweeps; alerts; RSS where available; third‑party mirrors.
• Delta Log — 'Old vs new' table with timestamps and screenshots.
• Critical Changes — Assignment shifts; sealed entries; clerical corrections.
• Action — File a Notice of Docket Change if it affects deadlines or posture.
• Archive — Save PDFs of the docket at milestones.
📝 Assignment
Create a Docket Delta Log and add the last two meaningful changes with screenshots and dates.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
DOCKET DELTA ROW
2025‑08‑28: Entry 51 edited (caption fix); screenshot Ex. A.

💡 Reflection
Seeing change is power; documenting change is leverage.

🎨 Visual Pairing
Split screen 'Docket v1' vs 'Docket v2' with a highlighted delta.



