Module 67
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 6 — Procedural Sovereignty
Module 67 – Summons & the Service Clock: Control the First 90 Days ⏳📜
⚖️ Core Message
Early missteps cost the most. Master issuance, delivery, and re‑service options so the case starts on rails.

📖 Lesson Content
• Issuance — Correct caption + party list; track when the clock starts.
• Delivery Plan — Who serves whom, by when; backup methods; substitutions where allowed.
• Returns — Affidavits precise and legible; cross‑reference with receipts.
• Re‑service — Cure defects quickly; file notice of corrective actions.
• Calendar — 90‑day master plan with weekly checks.
📝 Assignment
Draft a 'Service Plan' for a hypothetical complaint with 3 defendants in different locations; include contingencies.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
SERVICE PLAN (EXCERPT)
D1: personal; D2: certified mail + email stip; D3: process server; re‑service window planned 30–45 days.

💡 Reflection
The opening 90 days teach the court how you run the case.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A 90‑day bar with milestones: Issuance → Delivery → Returns → Cure.



