Module 68
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 6 — Procedural Sovereignty
Module 68 – Default Guardrails: Win the Record, Not Just the Clock 🚧⏰
⚖️ Core Message
Default is leverage, not a shortcut. Ensure proper notice, clean affidavits, and a narrow proposed order that can survive later scrutiny.

📖 Lesson Content
• Notice Proof — Multiple channels + declaration; avoid 'gotcha' service.
• Affidavits — Clear facts with exhibits; avoid conclusions.
• Relief Scope — Tailor default orders; resist overbroad remedies.
• Cure Offers — Document reasonable extensions or meet‑and‑confer attempts.
• Appeal Shield — Findings and pin‑cites lower reversal risk.
📝 Assignment
Draft a default judgment packet: affidavit with exhibits, proposed findings, and a narrow order.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
PROPOSED FINDINGS (EXCERPT)
Service on 06/12 (Ex. A); No response by 07/12; Notice email 07/05 (Ex. B); Relief limited to X.

💡 Reflection
A careful default now saves months later.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A narrow bridge labeled 'Default Order' over a chasm labeled 'Overreach'.



