Module 69
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 6 — Procedural Sovereignty
Module 69 – Mirror Archives: Notion/GitHub/Drive Sync 🔁🗃️
⚖️ Core Message
Sovereignty means sources can’t vanish with one account. Mirror archives across platforms with the same slugs and hashes.

📖 Lesson Content
• Three Mirrors — Narrative (Notion) + Files/Hashes (GitHub) + Heavy PDFs (Drive).
• Slugs — YYYY‑MM‑DD_ShortSlug.pdf across mirrors.
• Sync Cycle — Monthly mirror check with hash comparisons.
• Downtime — Offline backups; export Notion; tag releases in GitHub.
• Public Map — 'Where everything lives' in README.
📝 Assignment
Publish a mirror plan: list mirrors, sync frequency, and how to verify integrity.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
SYNC NOTE
GitHub tag v1.2.0; Drive folder 'Public_v1.2.0'; Notion page updated; hashes match manifest.

💡 Reflection
Mirrors make your record durable beyond any one platform.

🎨 Visual Pairing
Three icons linked by a looped arrow; a checkmark overlays each.



