Module 70
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 6 — Procedural Sovereignty
Module 70 – Pre‑Drafted Orders: Libraries that Accelerate Relief 📚✅
⚖️ Core Message
Judges grant what they can sign. Keep a library of clean, narrow orders for recurring asks so you always attach a decision‑ready option.

📖 Lesson Content
• Order Library — TRO A/B; accept corrected filing; status call; clarify findings.
• Style — Short captions, numbered relief, dates/limits; no argument in orders.
• Variants — Federal/state versions; with/without bond; timelines included.
• Index — One‑pager listing which order template matches which motion.
• Maintenance — Version numbers; small diff notes.
📝 Assignment
Create a four‑order library (A/B for accept‑or‑cure; status call; clarify findings) with a one‑page index.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
[PROPOSED] ORDER (EXCERPT)
Option A: Accept corrected filing nunc pro tunc to [date]. Option B: Issue deficiency list within 3 days.

💡 Reflection
A signable page is often the shortest path to yes.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A drawer labeled 'Orders' with neatly tabbed templates.



