Tier 6 — Procedural Sovereignty
Module 73 – Motion Libraries & Snippets: Reduce Draft Time ✂️⚙️
⚖️ Core Message
Maintain reusable motion skeletons and argument snippets tied to your record and standards of review.

📖 Lesson Content
• Skeletons — TRO, clarify findings, accept corrected filing, stay pending appeal.
• Snippets — One‑paragraph standards with cites ready to drop in.
• Variables — Bracket placeholders for dates, ECF cites, exhibit labels.
• QA — Snippet log with last‑used date and errors fixed.
• Storage — Keep a single 'motions' folder with an index.
📝 Assignment
Create a 'Motion Snippet Index' with at least five standard paragraphs ready for reuse.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
SNIPPET — Winter Standard (9th Cir.)…

💡 Reflection
Good writing is often good pasting of the right, verified snippet.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A toolbox labeled 'Snippets' next to a document with bracketed fields.



