Module 74
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 6 — Procedural Sovereignty
Module 74 – Template Governance: QA that Prevents Copy‑Paste Errors 🧪🧰
⚖️ Core Message
Templates help until they hurt. A light QA step—cites, names, dates, captions—prevents embarrassing and harmful mistakes.

📖 Lesson Content
• Four‑Point QA — Captions, names, dates, cites; check each with a finger trace.
• QA Buddy — A fresh set of eyes; 5‑minute pass before filing.
• Diffs — Compare v1.1.0 to v1.1.1; note meaningful changes.
• Kill Switch — If wrong, file a 'Correction Notice' within the hour; own it.
• Archive — Keep the pre‑ and post‑fix versions with hashes.
📝 Assignment
Add a QA checklist to your filing SOP and perform it on your last motion before re‑uploading.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
QA CHECK
Caption OK • Names OK • Dates OK • Cites OK • Hash: 3f2c…

💡 Reflection
QA is humility in action—and it saves reputation.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A small checklist card stamped 'QA' with four checkmarks.



