Module 75
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 6 — Procedural Sovereignty
Module 75 – Local Rules Parsers: Turn Rules into Checklists 📜✅
⚖️ Core Message
Local rules stop filings more than statutes do. Parse them into simple checklists and attach the checklist to your motion packet.

📖 Lesson Content
• Parse — Page limits; fonts; conferral; exhibits; hearing requests.
• Translate — Each requirement into a checkbox line.
• Attach — Include a 'Local Rules Compliance Statement' in your filing.
• Update — Re‑parse when rules change; keep a version and date.
• Share — Publish your checklist so others can reuse it.
📝 Assignment
Create a local‑rules checklist for one court and attach it to your next filing as a compliance statement.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
COMPLIANCE STATEMENT
This motion complies with LR 7.1 page limits (14 pages), font, and conferral (Ex. A).

💡 Reflection
Checklists are the antidote to accidental non‑compliance.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A rulebook icon becoming a checklist with green ticks.



