Module 76
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 6 — Procedural Sovereignty
Module 76 – Communications Protocol: Clerk/Judge Contact within the Rules 📬📞
⚖️ Core Message
Communication is procedural. Know when you can email or call, what to say, and how to memorialize it in the record without crossing lines.

📖 Lesson Content
• Clerk Channels — Public phone lines; filing portal messages; never ex parte merits.
• Chambers Etiquette — If permitted, logistics only; confirm in writing.
• Memorialize — File Notices of Communication with dates, topics, and non‑substantive nature.
• Tone — Factual, respectful, brief; attach proof of any instruction received.
• Boundaries — When in doubt, ask how to proceed on‑record.
📝 Assignment
Draft a 'Clerk Communication SOP' (what/when/how) and a Notice of Communication template.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
NOTICE OF COMMUNICATION
On 09/02 at 10:14, I spoke with Clerk X regarding docket entry timing; no merits discussed. See Ex. A (email follow‑up).

💡 Reflection
Clear, logged communications prevent confusion and protect everyone involved.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A small phone/email icon feeding a 'Notice of Communication' document.



