📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 6 — Procedural Sovereignty
Module 77 – Process Server Playbook: Field‑Ready Instructions 🧭👟
⚖️ Core Message
Turn service into a repeatable operation: clear instructions, contact script, and a proof package returned every time.

📖 Lesson Content
• Packet — Summons, complaint, exhibits, map, contact sheet; deadlines bolded.
• Script — What to say/do if declined; alternate times/locations.
• Proof — Photos/time stamps; affidavit template; chain‑of‑custody for documents.
• Payment — Confirm fees and receipts; vendor W‑9 if needed.
• Aftercare — Review proof same day; file COS promptly.
📝 Assignment
Write a one‑page 'Process Server Instructions' sheet and a return‑proof checklist.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
SERVER INSTRUCTIONS (EXCERPT)
Serve [Name] at [Addr]; best hours 9–11am; if refused, attempt 7pm; call immediately; take time‑stamped photo of doorplate.

💡 Reflection
Good instructions turn strangers into teammates.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A clipboard with 'Serve' checklist and a small map pin.



