Module 78
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 6 — Procedural Sovereignty
Module 78 – Service by Publication: When, How, and With What Proof 📰📜
⚖️ Core Message
Publication is a last resort—win it with a record of diligent search, proposed text, and a declaration that nails the elements.

📖 Lesson Content
• Diligence — Affidavit of due diligence: attempts, searches, contacts.
• Proposal — Publication text: parties, court, relief, response deadline.
• Venues — Approved newspapers/websites; frequency/duration.
• Proof — Tear sheets/affidavits from publisher; attach to motion and COS.
• Sunset — Ask for limited scope; proceed to judgment only on noticed claims.
📝 Assignment
Draft a Motion for Service by Publication with a diligence declaration and a proposed publication text.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
PUBLICATION TEXT (EXCERPT)
To: [Defendant]. You are notified that… Response due [date]. Case [number], Court [name].

💡 Reflection
If you show you tried everything else, judges say yes more easily.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A small newspaper icon with text highlighted; a stamp 'Due Diligence' next to it.



