Module 79
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 6 — Procedural Sovereignty
Module 79 – Subpoena Strategy: Narrow Targets, Clear Custodians 📑🎯
⚖️ Core Message
Subpoenas are surgical tools—name the custodian, specify records, offer reasonable time and format, and prepare to move to enforce or quash.

📖 Lesson Content
• Custodian Focus — Name the person/office; avoid fishing expeditions.
• Specificity — Date ranges, keywords, formats; exclude privileged material.
• Service & Fees — Proper service; witness fees if required; proof of tender.
• Motion Practice — Anticipate enforce/quash; propose a narrowed compromise.
• Privacy — Protect PII/PHI; use protective orders where needed.
📝 Assignment
Draft a Rule 45 subpoena (or state analog) with a custodian declaration and a narrowed scope statement.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
SCOPE (EXCERPT)
Emails to/from [custodian] between 05/01–08/01 regarding '[case number]' and 'deficiency'.

💡 Reflection
Precision is persuasive; it also survives motions practice.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A target icon over a folder labeled 'Custodian Records'.



