Module 80
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 6 — Procedural Sovereignty
Module 80 – Third‑Party Declarations: External Proof that Travels 🧾🤝
⚖️ Core Message
Third‑party declarations (IT, mailroom, process server, patient) turn your timeline into shared memory—if they’re short, factual, and attached.

📖 Lesson Content
• Scope — Only what they know; dates/tools used; who received what.
• Format — § 1746 language; exhibits; contact info for verification.
• Chain — Hash their PDFs; index in your ledger; cross‑cite everywhere you use them.
• Tone — Neutral and specific; avoid opinions/legal conclusions.
• Follow‑up — Keep permissions; update if facts change.
📝 Assignment
Draft a one‑page third‑party declaration (mailroom or IT) authenticating a receipt or error log.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
DECLARATION (IT)
I maintain the portal logs; the attached record shows error code 502 at 18:04 on 07/10… /s/ [Name].

💡 Reflection
Neutral third parties make your story verifiable.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A small badge icon next to a short declaration with a paperclip.



