Module 82
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 6 — Procedural Sovereignty
Module 82 – Settlement Windows: Freeze Harm, Keep Leverage 🤝🧊
⚖️ Core Message
Use short standstills and status orders to freeze harm while talks proceed; protect your clocks and record the terms.

📖 Lesson Content
• Standstill — Narrow standstill stip; no waiver of deadlines without clarity.
• Status Order — Ask court to adopt timelines; keep enforcement hook.
• Without Prejudice — Protect positions; reserve rights.
• Minutes — File a short status minute post‑call to avoid drift.
• Deadlines — If talks stall, resume cadence immediately.
📝 Assignment
Draft a 2‑page standstill stipulation and a proposed status order with a 14‑day check‑in.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
STANDSTILL (EXCERPT)
Parties agree to pause X action for 14 days; no waiver of rights; status call on [date].

💡 Reflection
Good settlements happen when clocks are clear and harm is paused.

🎨 Visual Pairing
Two hands shaking over a small hourglass frozen mid‑flow.



