Module 83
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 6 — Procedural Sovereignty
Module 83 – Post‑Judgment Toolkit: Costs, Interest, Enforcement 🧰⚖️
⚖️ Core Message
If judgment enters, sovereignty shifts to enforcement: costs, interest calculations, liens, and orders to show cause for compliance.

📖 Lesson Content
• Costs — Timely bill; allowable items; forms; objections process.
• Interest — Post‑judgment rates; calculate clearly; attach worksheets.
• Enforcement — Orders to show cause; writs; narrow contempt paths.
• Negotiation — Payment plans; security; satisfaction of judgment filing.
• Record — File proof of satisfaction when paid.
📝 Assignment
Draft a costs bill + interest worksheet and a short OSC to compel compliance with a narrow remedy.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
OSC (EXCERPT)
Respondent to show cause within 14 days why [narrow action] has not occurred; attach proof…

💡 Reflection
Enforcement is procedure with math—be precise and proportionate.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A calculator icon next to a short order labeled 'OSC'.



