Module 84
📘 Legal Calculus 4.5
Tier 6 — Procedural Sovereignty
Module 84 – Exit & Relay: Handoff to Counsel or Amici Without Losing Memory 🔚📦
⚖️ Core Message
When you hand off, preserve sovereignty by packaging the record, the calendar, and the coalition map so others can act immediately.

📖 Lesson Content
• Handoff Pack — One‑pager 'How to Run This'; index of folders; credential pass‑off steps.
• Calendar — Deadlines + buffers + status cadence.
• Record — Hash manifest; Top‑10; master declaration; link map.
• Coalition — Contacts; asks; status; next steps.
• Post‑Exit — Where updates live; who maintains mirrors.
📝 Assignment
Create an Exit & Relay folder (How‑To, Calendar, Hash Manifest, Contacts) and a README linking to public mirrors.

✅ Model Answer (Template)
HOW‑TO (EXCERPT)
Where everything lives; how to verify; who to contact; how to publish updates.

💡 Reflection
A graceful exit is a public good—and the best way to protect the work.

🎨 Visual Pairing
A labeled box with files: HOW‑TO.md, CALENDAR.ics, HASHES.txt, CONTACTS.csv.

